text:
When trying to include the results of a JSP page in a Servlet, Tomcat fails.  It 
will include the content of an HTML page, but not the content of a JSP page.  
Use the code below in a servlet ... the html page will work, the JSP page will 
not.

THIS WORKS:
RequestDispatcher rd =  null;
rd = req.getRequestDispatcher("/jsp/test.html");
rd.include(req, res);

THIS DOES *NOT* WORK:
RequestDispatcher rd =  null;
rd = req.getRequestDispatcher("/jsp/test.jsp");
rd.include(req, res);

The file "test.html" and "test.jsp" can be the identical file with different 
extentions (html or jsp).  The html page is served by the web server and its 
contents are included in the Servlet just fine.  The JSP page is interpreted by 
Tomcat and its contents are *not* included in the Servlet.  The JSP page can be 
executed successfully by calling it directly.  However, if called from within a 
RequestDispatcher.include(req,res) call in a Servlet, the output of the JSP is 
not included in the Servlet results.
